His dyett at table was for all such as thither resorted, plentifull and good, but for himself veric meane. For upon such eating daies as were not fasted, although he would for his health use a larger dyet then at other times, yet was it with such temperance, that comonly he was wont to cate and drinke by waight and measure. And the most of his sustinance was thinne pottasse, sodden with ssesh, eating of the flesh it seli verie sparingely.
